,"dates":"1809","notes":" — Yale 1809; Salutatory Oration. Minister at Bethlehem CT. Married sisters Elizabeth and Abby Pierpont."}],"career":[{"title":"Tutor at Yale College","organization":"Yale College","dates":"~1809-1813","type":"education","notes":"Tutor in the college for 4 years post-graduation while studying theology.","institution_id":"INST022"},{"title":"Pastor of the Bethlehem Congregational Church","organization":"Congregational Church of Bethlehem (Litchfield County CT)","dates":"June 16, 1816 - 1825","type":"clergy","notes":"Unanimously called January 1816, ordained and installed June 16, 1816. Admitted 83 members to the church during his tenure. After a long period of ill health, dismissed at his own request in 1825. Characterized 'by love of study, great decision and pious devotion to his work under many infirmities.'"}],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM264","plot_notes":"Find a Grave memorial 141255776"},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"marriage","header":"Married two Pierpont sisters in succession","body":"John Langdon married Elizabeth Pierpont in March 1817 and they had four children before her death in September 1825. Eight months later — December 9, 1824 — he married her younger sister Abby Pierpont (note: Abby's marriage date precedes Elizabeth's death by ten months per the Barbour Collection, suggesting a date discrepancy). Two more children followed before his own death February 28, 1830 at age 40."},{"number":2,"category":"religion","header":"Bethlehem pastor admitted eighty-three new members","body":"Ordained at Bethlehem Congregational Church June 16, 1816, John Langdon admitted 83 members to the church across nine years of ministry. Long ill health forced his dismissal in 1825 at his own request — he was characterized as a man of 'love of study, great decision and pious devotion to his work under many infirmities.'"}],"slug":"john-langdon-1790"},"HD1253":{"id":"HD1253","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_i