es at Yale, the institution his own family had helped found."},{"number":2,"category":"marriage","header":"Three brothers snowbound — three sisters married","body":"Three Pierpont brothers journeying through Litchfield County stopped overnight at the Collins home in South Farms when a great storm stranded them for weeks. All three married daughters of the family: Robert married Lois Collins, his brother Evelyn married her sister Rhoda, and their brother James married a third sister."},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"Yale alumnus turned Yale College employee","body":"Evelyn was a Revolutionary War officer and a Yale College graduate who settled as a farmer at Litchfield Connecticut after the war. Reduced in circumstances late in life, he returned to Yale — not as alumnus but as employee — and continued in such service until his death."}],"bio":{"display_name":"Lt. Evelyn Pierpont","first_name":"Evelyn","last_name":"Pierpont","title":"Lieutenant","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022","relationship":"alumnus"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"evelyn-pierpont-1755"},"X00324":{"id":"X00324","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":[],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1764,"month":10,"day":5,"city":"Litchfield","county":"Litchfield","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1845,"month":6,"day":20,"city":"Livonia","county":"Livingston","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"gender":"female","parents":{"father_id":"X02136","mother_id":"X02137"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H00351","children_ids":["H00809","H00810","H00811","